═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Before running 'git add .':
  [ ] .gitignore file is present
  [ ] jasoos_env/ folder exists (will be ignored)
  [ ] No .env files with secrets
  [ ] No api_keys.txt file
  [ ] All Python files intact
  [ ] All documentation files intact
  [ ] requirements.txt present

After running 'git status':
  [ ] All .py files shown as new files
  [ ] All .md files shown as new files
  [ ] requirements.txt shown as new file
  [ ] .gitignore shown as new file
  [ ] jasoos_env/ NOT listed (ignored)
  [ ] __pycache__/ NOT listed (ignored)
  [ ] logs/ NOT listed (ignored)
  [ ] No secret files listed

After push:
  [ ] All files on GitHub
  [ ] Repository size ~200 KB (not 150+ MB)
  [ ] .gitignore visible on GitHub
  [ ] No venv folder on GitHub
  [ ] No cache on GitHub


═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Summary:
  .gitignore = "Don't upload these files/folders"
  It's already in your outputs folder
  It's already configured correctly
  It will automatically prevent uploading venv, cache, logs, secrets

Result: Clean, small GitHub repository ready for production!

